# ── Author trailing-slash note ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PROBLEM: The live agenta.ai canonical for author profile pages is
#   /authors/<slug>/   (WITH trailing slash)
# but wrangler.jsonc sets html_handling: "drop-trailing-slash", which forces
# a 308 redirect from /authors/<slug>/ → /authors/<slug> (no slash) for ALL
# paths globally. A _redirects rule of the form:
#   /authors/:slug   /authors/:slug/   308
# would create a redirect LOOP: Cloudflare would immediately drop the slash
# again before serving the asset. _redirects rules and html_handling both run
# at the Workers asset layer, with html_handling taking precedence for trailing-
# slash normalization.
#
# SOLUTION (must be wired at deploy time):
# Add a Cloudflare Zone-level Transform Rule (URL Rewrite) in the dashboard:
#   Match:  URI Path matches regex  ^/authors/[^/]+$   (no trailing slash)
#   Action: Rewrite URL → concat(http.request.uri.path, "/")
#
# This rewrites the URL *before* it hits the Worker asset handler, so the
# Worker sees the slash path and serves /authors/<slug>/index.html without
# triggering its own trailing-slash redirect. Because the rewrite is
# transparent (not a redirect), the browser canonical stays /authors/<slug>/
# which matches the live site.
#
# Until that Transform Rule is wired, /authors/<slug>/ will 308 to /authors/<slug>
# (no slash) at the Cloudflare edge — the page still loads, but the canonical
# diverges from the live site (minor SEO gap, not a content gap).
#
# Transform Rule location:
#   Cloudflare dashboard → agenta.ai zone → Rules → Transform Rules → URL Rewrite
#
# Alternative (simpler, at Workers layer, no dashboard access needed):
# Change html_handling to "auto-trailing-slash" — Cloudflare will then
# preserve existing trailing slashes, emit trailing-slash URLs for /authors/*,
# and still serve non-slash URLs for all other pages (it reads the HTML to
# decide). This is the recommended setting for mixed trailing-slash sites.
# Only reason we have not flipped it: risk of unintended behaviour on the
# other 45 pages. Test before switching.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
